author: Gary Pinneo
title: High School Sports: Penn Yan Volleyball wins FL East crown; girls soccer falls in sectional play
text: Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 12:17 PM By Gary Pinneo Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 12:17 PM Penn Yan Volleyball: Penn Yan Mustangs win Finger Lakes East title The Penn Yan Mustang volleyball team defeated Waterloo 3-1 Thursday afternoon. The win gave the Mustangs a share of the Finger Lakes East League title. They are co-champions with Wayne. Both teams finished their regular season with 10-2 records in the league. Penn Yan enjoyed a 15-2 record overall. Penn Yan wins the Finger Lakes East crown for the first time since 1986. Thursday's Mustang win was sparked by Emily Wunder's 15 kills, 3 aces, 4 blocks, and 9 digs. Kelly Bray dished out 23 assists, and added 10 digs and 2 aces. Jessie Decker recorded 4 kills, 4 aces, 3 blocks, and 5 digs. Jessica Covell accounted for 12 digs, and served 2 aces while teammate Brie Yonge added 13 digs. Sydney Bloom added 10 kills, 1 aces, 3 blocks, and 6 digs. The regular season ends on a fantastic high note for the Mustang volleyball team. High School Soccer: Penn Yan, Marcus Whitman eliminated from Girl's Sectional Tournament The Section V Girl's Soccer tournament opened Friday for two local high school teams. Unfortunately for both teams, it was a short ride. Pal-Mac shut out Penn Yan 4-0 in Palmyra and the Marcus Whitman Wildcats dropped a 3-0 decision to LeRoy. The Class B1 # 5 seed Penn Yan Mustangs end their season with a 5-13 record. Marcus Whitman, the #5 seed in Class B2, finishes with a 5-13 record also. By Gary Pinneo
